Authors: Irwansyah E., Faisal M., Primadini A.
Title: Does efficient Fuzzy Kohonen clustering network algorithm really improves clustering data result?
Source title: Journal of Theoretical and Applied Information Technology
Affiliations: Department of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jalan KH. Syahdan No. 9, Palmerah Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Department of Electrical Engineering, University of Indonesia, Depok, 16424, Indonesia
Authors with affiliations: Irwansyah, E., Department of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jalan KH. Syahdan No. 9, Palmerah Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Faisal, M., Department of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jalan KH. Syahdan No. 9, Palmerah Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Primadini, A., Department of Electrical Engineering, University of Indonesia, Depok, 16424, Indonesia
Abstract: In this research, Fuzzy Kohonen Clustering Network (FKCN) algorithm is compared to Efficient Fuzzy Kohonen Clustering Network (EFKCN) algorithm. This research is conducted to see if EFKCN is really efficient and could do a better clustering analysis than original FKCN. We do empirical testing and simulations to compare both algorithms, by using an expanded Fisher’s Iris Data. The result showed the accuracy of EFKCN is not yet better algorithm rather than FKCN. © 2005 - 2015 JATIT & LLS. All rights reserved.

Title: Building damage hazard zonation using FKCN and IDW algorithm
Source title: Journal of Theoretical and Applied Information Technology
Affiliations: Dept of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jalan KH. Syahdan No. 9 Palmerah, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia
Authors with affiliations: Faisal, M., Dept of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jalan KH. Syahdan No. 9 Palmerah, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Irwansyah, E., Dept of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jalan KH. Syahdan No. 9 Palmerah, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia
Abstract: The objective of this study is to create building damage hazard zonation area using fuzzy kohonen clustering network (FKCN) for physical parameter data clustering and inverse distance weighting (IDW) for data interpolation in Banda Aceh city, Indonesia. IDW algorithm is used alongside FKCN because of its simplicity. The physical parameter in this study consists of lithology, topographic zone and peak ground acceleration value (PGA). The result is Banda Aceh city divided into 3 zones which are low, medium, and high building damage area, based on the combination of physical parameter on each area. © 2005 - 2014 JATIT & LLS. All rights reserved.
Author Keywords: Building damage; Earthquake; Fuzzy kohonen clustering network; Hazard zonation; Inverse distance weighting
